eptibility based on the\noverlap density converges to a finite value which is an increasing function of\nthe density. The distribution function behind these dynamical four-point\ncorrelations and its extension to three-dimensional cases, respecting the\ntensorial character of the two-particle displacement correlation, are also\ndiscussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 31 Dec 2012 18:55:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 22 Jan 2013 17:18:05 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 13 Aug 2013 01:32:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-12-06"}
