 the H$_2$ run, which results in slightly higher SFRD at\nlow-redshift due to more abundant gas available for star formation at later\ntimes. This new H$_2$ model is able to reproduce the empirical KS relationship\nat $z=0$ naturally without the need for setting its normalization by hand, and\noverall it seems to have more advantages than the previous pressure-based SF\nmodel.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Jan 2013 06:57:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Dec 2013 08:40:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
